<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="295" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="0.[136,1452,1800,2007]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,192,1800,1826]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">Note</emphasis>
: 
<bibRefCitation author="Franchet, A. R." box="[208,447,1800,1827]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295" pagination="253 - 266" refId="ref2081" refString="Franchet, A. R. (1899) Plantarum sinensium ecloge tertia. Journal de Botanique 13 (8): 253 - 266." type="journal article" year="1899">Franchet (1899: 255)</bibRefCitation>
in the protologue of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Franchet" authorityYear="1899" box="[689,854,1800,1826]" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Abies" kingdom="Plantae" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="295" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="delavayi">
<emphasis box="[689,854,1800,1826]" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">Abies delavayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mentioned only the collection of Delavay “n. 1210” from Yunnan. 
<bibRefCitation author="Liu, T. J." box="[293,469,1836,1862]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295" refId="ref2304" refString="Liu, T. J. (1971) A monograph of the genus Abies. Department of Forestry, College of Agriculture, National Taiwan University, Taipei." type="book" year="1971">Liu (1971: 141)</bibRefCitation>
indicated that “The type (Delavay no. 1210) is preserved in the herbarium of 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:0384A2620774FFBCFF56A21DA528F854:8EF245AF0774FFBCFAF7A367A79AF8E8" country="France" name="Museum de Paris" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">Museum de Paris</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[207,292,1872,1898]" name="France" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">France</collectingCountry>
.”, an effective first-step lectotypification under Art. 9.17. 
<bibRefCitation author="Farjon, A." box="[939,1095,1872,1898]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295" refId="ref1957" refString="Farjon, A. (2017) A handbook of the world's conifers. 2 nd ed. Brill, Leiden &amp; Boston, 1154 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1163 / 9789004324510" type="book" year="2017">Farjon (2017)</bibRefCitation>
later indicated “Delavay 1210” in P as “ 
<typeStatus box="[227,330,1908,1934]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">holotype</typeStatus>
” of this name. There are, however, 
<specimenCount box="[730,897,1908,1935]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of this gathering at P (with barcodes P00748883, P00748884). As Farjon did not effectively select a second-step 
<typeStatus box="[843,946,1944,1970]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">lectotype</typeStatus>
(Art. 7.11), we select P00748883, displaying cones, as the second-step 
<typeStatus box="[425,528,1980,2006]" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">lectotype</typeStatus>
(
<figureCitation box="[543,608,1980,2006]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[136,229,2028,2050]" captionTargetBox="[227,1366,211,2000]" captionTargetId="figure-17@1.[203,1385,187,2001]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Abies delavayi Franch. (lectotype). © MNHN collection-Paris." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6650935" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6650935/files/figure.png" pageId="0" pageNumber="295">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
